      • addBoolean

        public ConfigElementBoolean addBoolean(String id,
                                       Boolean defaultValue,
                                       AbstractDisplayOption displayOption)
        Adds a new Boolean attribute to the registry. The attribute will be globally registered and will be saved and loaded as part of the node configuration. This attribute can later be accessed under the given id, e.g. NodeConfiguration.getBoolean(String).
        Parameters:
        id - The unique ID in this configuration tree.
        defaultValue - The default value.
        displayOption - Optional display options (may be null)
        Returns:
        An config element that represents the attribute. Most implementations will ignore this return value.

      • addConfigElement

        public <T extends AbstractConfigElement> T addConfigElement(T configElement)
        Adds a configuration parameter to the registry and returns it.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of parameter
        Parameters:
        configElement - The element itself.
        Returns:
        The method argument. Allows for inline instantiation, e.g. ConfigElementInt c = registry.addConfigElement(new ConfigElementInt(...);
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If called after configuration tree construction.
        IllegalArgumentException - If there is a previously added config element with the same ID.
        NullPointerException - If the argument is null.

      • getConfigElement

        <T extends AbstractConfigElement> T getConfigElement(String id,
                                                     Class<T> cl)
                                              throws InvalidSettingsException
        Queries a config parameter previously registered with one of the add methods.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the parameter
        Parameters:
        id - The ID under which the parameter is registered
        cl - The class to T.
        Returns:
        The config element, never null.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - If the config parameter has not been registered or was registered under a different type.
        NullPointerException - If either argument is null.

      • internalCreateNew

        public static final ConfigRegistry internalCreateNew(String name)
        Factory method used by the framework to create a new empty config registry. This method must not be used by client code and may change in future versions.
        Parameters:
        name - The internally used ID for this config registry.
        Returns:
        A new config registry.
